transliteration: Gadgaddan Gadje Soubajje Sahoorain|| Kaagaddan Kavooyaan Katthe Kathoorain||37||114||
translation: There are loud shouts with porofound resoundings, and the poets describe them in their verses.37.114.

gurmukhi: cwgVdMg caupy bwgVdMg bIrM ] mwgVdMg mwry qnM iq`C qIrM ]
transliteration: Daagaddan Daano Bhaagaddan Bhaaje|| Gadgaddan Gadjoo Jaagaddan Gadje||
translation: The demons are running away and the heroes are shouting loudly.

gurmukhi: gwgVdMg g`jy sub`jy ghIrYN ] kwgVdMg kvIXwn k`Qy kQIrYN ]37]114]
transliteration: Chhaadaddan Chhauhoo Chhure Pre Chhadaake|| Taagaddan Tooran Toupkan Tadaake||38||115||
translation: The sounds are produced by the striking axes and daggers. The arrows and the guns are creating their own noses.38.115.

gurmukhi: gwgVdMg gomwX g`jy ghIrM ] swgVdMg sMKM nwgVdMg nPIrM ]
transliteration: Gadgaddan Gomaay Gadje Gadooran|| Saagaddan Sankhanndnaagaddan Naphooran||
translation: The loud noise of drums and the resounding of conches and trumpets is being heard in the battlefield.

gurmukhi: bwgVdMg bwjy b`jy bIr KyqM ] nwgVdMg nwcy su BUqM pryqM ]39]116]
transliteration: Baagaddan Baaje Bajje Boor Khetan|| Naagaddan Naache Su Bhootan Pretan||39||116||
translation: The musical instruments of the warriors are being played and the ghosts and goblins are dancing.39.116.

gurmukhi: qwgVdMg qIrM bwgVdMg bwxM ] kwgVdMg kwqI ktwrI kiRpwxM ]
transliteration: Taagaddan Tiran Baagaddan Baanan|| Kaagaddan Kaatoo Katdaroo Kridaanan||
translation: The noises of the arrows and shafts, daggers and swords are being heard.

gurmukhi: nwgVdMg nwdM bwgVdMg bwjy ] swgVdMg sUrM rwgVdMg rwjy ]40]117]
transliteration: Naagaddan Naadan Baagaddan Baaje|| Saagaddan Sooran Raagaddan Raaje||40||117||
translation: The music of the musical instruments and the drumming of the trumpets resounds and the warriors and chieftains are doing their job amidst such resonance.40.117.

gurmukhi: swgVdMg sMKM nwgVdMg nPIrM ] gwgVdMg gomwX g`jy ghIrM ]
transliteration: Saagaddan Sankhanndnaagaddan Naphooran|| Gadgaddan Gomaay Gadje Gadooran||
translation: The conches, clarionets and the drums resounded.

gurmukhi: nwgVdMg ngwry bwgVdMg bwjy ] jwgVdMg joDw gwgVdMg gwjy ]41]118]
transliteration: Naagaddan Nagdare Baagaddan Baaje|| Jaagaddan Jodhaa Gadgaddan Gadje||41||118||
translation: The trumpets and musical instruments produced their sounds and alongwith their resonance, the warriors thundered.41.118.

gurmukhi: ijqyk rUp DwrIXM ] iqqyk dyib mwrIXM ]
transliteration: Jitek Roop Dhdarooyan|| Titek Db(i) Marooyan||
translation: All the forms of demons created with the spilling of the blood of Rakat Beej on ground, were killed by the goddess.

gurmukhi: ijqyk rUp Dwr hIN ] iqiqE dRugw sMGwr hIN ]42]119]
transliteration: Jitek Roop Dhaar Hoon|| Titio Drougad Sanhaar Hoon||42||119||
translation: All the forms that are going to materialize, will also be destroyed by Durga.42.119.

gurmukhi: ijqyk ssqR vw Jry ] p√çwh sRon ky pry ]
transliteration: Jitek Sastra Vaa Jdare|| Pravaah Sron Ke Dare||
translation: With the showering of weapons (on Rakat Beej), the currents of blood ooxed out (from the body of Rakat Beej).

gurmukhi: ijqIik ibMdukw igrYN ] su pwn kwilkw krYN ]43]120]
transliteration: Jitook(i) Bindoukaa Girain|| Su Paan Kaalikaa Darain||43||120||
translation: All the drops that fell (on the ground), the goddess Kali drank them all.43.120.
